575
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:55,440
as some place which is so far away...

576
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:56,120
that it doesn't matter.

577
00:23:57,300 --> 00:23:58,580
And once we would...

578
00:23:58,580 --> 00:24:00,240
and that would mean...

579
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:01,800
that if that were possible...

580
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:02,620
you would say,

581
00:24:02,620 --> 00:24:02,880
well,

582
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:04,420
charge is conserved...

583
00:24:04,420 --> 00:24:05,220
but I would say,

584
00:24:05,220 --> 00:24:06,880
who cares if charge is conserved...

585
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:07,760
if it can just disappear?

586
00:24:08,120 --> 00:24:10,240
If it can just disappear arbitrarily...

587
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:11,360
to some very distant place...

588
00:24:12,220 --> 00:24:12,700
it's...

589
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:14,240
it's just as good as saying...

590
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:14,620
it didn't...

591
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:15,420
wasn't conserved.

592
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:17,140
In my laboratory...

593
00:24:17,140 --> 00:24:18,280
it just disappears.

594
00:24:19,020 --> 00:24:21,000
Charge doesn't disappear that way.

595
00:24:21,260 --> 00:24:23,180
If it leaves the laboratory...

596
00:24:23,180 --> 00:24:25,160
it passes through the walls of the laboratory.

597
00:24:25,660 --> 00:24:26,780
That means...

598
00:24:26,780 --> 00:24:27,880
it passes through windows.

599
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:31,400
That means it cannot leave the laboratory...

600
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:33,240
without a current flowing...

601
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:35,440
and that current has to flow out of the walls.

602
00:24:36,140 --> 00:24:37,180
That idea...

603
00:24:37,180 --> 00:24:38,480
is called continuity...

604
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:40,560
and there's an equation that goes with it.

605
00:24:41,620 --> 00:24:43,220
The equation is the continuity...

606
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:43,520
equation.

607
00:24:46,060 --> 00:24:47,860
If I take a little box...

608
00:24:49,460 --> 00:24:51,340
and I look at all the charges...

609
00:24:51,340 --> 00:24:53,120
passing out through the walls...

610
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:55,100
all the flow of charges...

611
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:57,160
passing out through the walls...

612
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,000
if I...

613
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:01,100
I'm interested in the charge per unit time...

614
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:03,800
that disappears out of the box...

615
00:25:05,820 --> 00:25:07,700
let's say it's a unit box...

616
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:10,400
then the amount of charge in that unit box...

617
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:11,820
is just sigma...

618
00:25:11,820 --> 00:25:13,220
if the volume is equal to one...

619
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,500
in some units...

620
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:17,520
the charge per unit time...

621
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:20,100
that is leaving the box...

622
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:21,240
is minus...

623
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:23,280
sigma dot.

624
00:25:23,580 --> 00:25:24,700
Why minus?

625
00:25:24,820 --> 00:25:26,220
Because it's leaving the box.

626
00:25:27,030 --> 00:25:28,620
If it's leaving the box...

627
00:25:28,620 --> 00:25:30,040
sigma is getting smaller.

628
00:25:30,910 --> 00:25:32,385
That has to be equal

629
00:25:32,385 --> 00:25:33,860
to the sum of the currents...

630
00:25:33,860 --> 00:25:35,290
passing out through the box...

631
00:25:35,780 --> 00:25:36,700
and by...

632
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:39,300
some Gauss theorem or something...

633
00:25:39,300 --> 00:25:41,560
that's just equal to the divergence...

634
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:42,540
of the current.

635
00:25:44,980 --> 00:25:46,520
The same current here.

636
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:49,020
The divergence of the current...

637
00:25:49,020 --> 00:25:50,840
is simply the total amount of current...

638
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:52,600
passing out of that small box...

639
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:54,420
the divergence of the current...

640
00:25:54,420 --> 00:25:54,860
inside...

641
00:25:54,860 --> 00:25:58,940
in the vicinity of the box...

642
00:26:00,420 --> 00:26:02,780
that's the current passing out...

643
00:26:02,780 --> 00:26:04,100
and this says...

644
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:05,500
that sigma dot...

645
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:07,460
is minus the divergence of the current.

646
00:26:08,220 --> 00:26:10,260
We can also write this of course...

647
00:26:10,260 --> 00:26:10,800
as...

648
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:12,440
well first of all we can write it as...

649
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:13,220
sigma dot plus...

650
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:15,280
the divergence of the current is equal to zero.

651
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:17,960
Sigma dot...

652
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,020
means...

653
00:26:19,020 --> 00:26:21,340
the derivative of sigma with respect...

654
00:26:21,340 --> 00:26:22,140
to time...

655
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:24,460
and this means...

656
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:27,100
the various components of the...

657
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:29,420
derivative of the current...

658
00:26:30,160 --> 00:26:31,360
with respect...

659
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:33,440
to the corresponding...

660
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:34,800
direction of space.

661
00:26:35,480 --> 00:26:37,300
So that current is...

662
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:38,440
a three vector current.

663
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:39,460
It's a three vector current.

664
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:42,540
Is equal to zero.

665
00:26:43,620 --> 00:26:45,220
And now...

666
00:26:45,220 --> 00:26:47,180
if I write that sigma...

667
00:26:47,180 --> 00:26:48,720
is J naught...

668
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:50,860
this just becomes...

669
00:26:50,860 --> 00:26:51,720
a nice elegant...

670
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:52,600
and that T...

671
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:56,780
is X naught...

672
00:26:56,780 --> 00:26:59,260
sigma is J naught...

673
00:26:59,260 --> 00:27:01,640
this just becomes a nice equation...

674
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:02,580
that...

675
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:05,200
derivative of Jm...

676
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:06,700
J mu...

677
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:08,960
space time index...

678
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,240
not just space index...

679
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:13,020
space time index J mu...

680
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:16,780
with respect to X mu...

681
00:27:17,780 --> 00:27:19,200
with respect to X mu...

682
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:22,240
is equal to zero.

683
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:23,420
Incidentally,

684
00:27:23,420 --> 00:27:25,260
I suppose if I wanted...

685
00:27:25,260 --> 00:27:27,100
to be really systematic...

686
00:27:27,100 --> 00:27:28,920
I would put a sum over M here.

687
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:31,700
Sigma dot...

688
00:27:31,700 --> 00:27:33,020
the sigma by DT...

689
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:35,470
plus sum on M...

690
00:27:36,500 --> 00:27:37,740
the J1...

691
00:27:37,740 --> 00:27:38,760
by the X1...

692
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,400
the J2 by the X2...

693
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:41,940
the J3 by the X3...

694
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:43,580
and that becomes...

695
00:27:43,580 --> 00:27:46,620
the derivative of J mu with respect to X mu...

696
00:27:46,620 --> 00:27:48,780
where I have now used the summation convention.

697
00:27:49,980 --> 00:27:50,540
Here...

698
00:27:50,540 --> 00:27:52,660
summation convention implied...

699
00:27:52,660 --> 00:27:53,600
or implicit...

700
00:27:55,360 --> 00:27:56,400
same thing...

701
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,140
is equal to zero.

702
00:27:57,220 --> 00:28:00,400
So it becomes a nice tensor type equation...

703
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:06,500
J is a four vector...

704
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:08,200
X...

705
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:10,800
four components of space...

706
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:12,040
and...

707
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:15,120
this has the nice look of a...

708
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:16,420
good equation...

709
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:20,620
the derivative of a tensor...

710
00:28:20,620 --> 00:28:22,280
with respect to position.

711
00:28:25,740 --> 00:28:27,260
In curved coordinates...

712
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:31,120
in general if you had a thing like this...

713
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:32,620
in curved coordinates...

714
00:28:32,620 --> 00:28:35,500
this would be correct in ordinary coordinates...

715
00:28:35,500 --> 00:28:37,460
in curved coordinates...

716
00:28:37,460 --> 00:28:39,200
you might replace this...

717
00:28:39,200 --> 00:28:40,540
by...

718
00:28:41,419 --> 00:28:43,140
the covariant derivative.

719
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:45,100
the covariant derivative.

720
00:28:45,100 --> 00:28:47,340
Remember about covariant derivatives of tensors...

721
00:28:47,340 --> 00:28:48,460
It turns out...

722
00:28:48,460 --> 00:28:49,800
in this case it doesn't matter...

723
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:51,720
for charge currents it doesn't matter...

724
00:28:51,720 --> 00:28:54,140
but in general it would matter...

725
00:28:54,140 --> 00:28:56,660
when you go to curved coordinates...

726
00:28:56,660 --> 00:28:58,420
you should replace all derivatives...

727
00:28:58,420 --> 00:28:59,480
by covariant derivatives.

728
00:29:03,960 --> 00:29:04,640
Otherwise...

729
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:06,380
the equations are not good...

730
00:29:06,380 --> 00:29:07,120
tensor equations.

731
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:09,580
Why do you want tensor equations?

732
00:29:09,780 --> 00:29:11,160
You want tensor equations because...

733
00:29:11,160 --> 00:29:12,340
you want them to be

734
00:29:12,340 --> 00:29:13,520
true in any set of coordinates.

735
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:19,760
Alright,

736
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:21,460
so anyway that's the theory of...

737
00:29:21,460 --> 00:29:22,880
electric charge...

738
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:23,540
flow...

739
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:24,820
current...

740
00:29:24,820 --> 00:29:26,840
and the continuity equation.

741
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:29,060
This is called the continuity equation...

742
00:29:29,060 --> 00:29:31,150
and the physics of it

743
00:29:31,150 --> 00:29:33,240
is that when charge either reappears...

744
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:34,060
sorry...

745
00:29:34,060 --> 00:29:36,900
appears or disappears in a small volume...

746
00:29:37,120 --> 00:29:39,080
it is always traceable to...

747
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:41,060
currents flowing into or out...

748
00:29:41,060 --> 00:29:43,000
through the boundaries of that region.

749
00:29:43,920 --> 00:29:45,200
Now let's come...

750
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,180
to energy and momentum.

751
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:49,100
Energy and momentum are also conserved...

752
00:29:49,100 --> 00:29:49,580
quantities.

753
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,220
They can be described...

754
00:29:55,220 --> 00:29:57,220
in terms of density of energy...

755
00:29:58,379 --> 00:29:59,940
density of momentum...

756
00:29:59,940 --> 00:30:01,280
density of each component...

757
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:01,800
of momentum.

758
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:04,420
You can ask how much...

759
00:30:05,399 --> 00:30:06,080
energy...

760
00:30:07,120 --> 00:30:08,200
is in the form of particles

761
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:09,280
or whatever it happens to be...

762
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:11,020
including the...

763
00:30:11,020 --> 00:30:12,500
mc squared part of the energy.

764
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:15,680
You can ask how much energy is in a volume...

765
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:17,100
You can ask how much...

766
00:30:17,100 --> 00:30:18,620
momentum is in a volume...

767
00:30:18,620 --> 00:30:20,520
Just look at all the particles within a volume...

768
00:30:20,520 --> 00:30:21,400
and count up their momentum.

769
00:30:23,260 --> 00:30:25,260
Photons or electromagnetic radiation...

770
00:30:25,260 --> 00:30:27,020
has both energy and momentum...

771
00:30:27,020 --> 00:30:28,680
and that energy and momentum...

772
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:31,080
can be regarded as...

773
00:30:32,340 --> 00:30:33,460
the integral...

774
00:30:33,460 --> 00:30:34,300
of a density.

775
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:37,080
So in that sense...

776
00:30:37,120 --> 00:30:39,220
each one of them...

777
00:30:39,220 --> 00:30:39,800
each...

778
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:40,940
the energy...

779
00:30:40,940 --> 00:30:42,860
and each component...

780
00:30:42,860 --> 00:30:44,120
of the momentum...

781
00:30:44,120 --> 00:30:46,100
are like the charge.

782
00:30:46,420 --> 00:30:47,900
They're conserved...

783
00:30:47,900 --> 00:30:49,180
they can flow...

784
00:30:49,180 --> 00:30:52,880
If an object or a thing is moving...

785
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:54,780
then the momentum and energy...

786
00:30:54,780 --> 00:30:55,780
may be flowing...

787
00:30:55,780 --> 00:30:57,620
and the question is how do

788
00:30:57,620 --> 00:30:59,460
we represent the same set of ideas...

789
00:30:59,860 --> 00:31:01,280
for energy and momentum.

790
00:31:01,880 --> 00:31:02,680
Now...

791
00:31:02,680 --> 00:31:04,120
there's a difference...

792
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:06,340
between charge...

793
00:31:07,120 --> 00:31:08,100
and energy and momentum.

794
00:31:09,459 --> 00:31:10,860
Electric charge...

795
00:31:10,860 --> 00:31:12,640
is an invariant.

796
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:15,220
No matter how the charge...

797
00:31:15,220 --> 00:31:16,080
is moving...

798
00:31:17,100 --> 00:31:19,060
the charge of an electron...

799
00:31:19,060 --> 00:31:20,000
is always the same.

800
00:31:21,100 --> 00:31:23,340
The charge of an electron...

801
00:31:23,340 --> 00:31:24,760
does not depend on its...

802
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:25,660
state of motion.

803
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:28,560
Therefore charge itself...

804
00:31:28,560 --> 00:31:29,760
is an invariant.

805
00:31:30,850 --> 00:31:32,100
Charge is invariant...

806
00:31:32,100 --> 00:31:32,920
the...

807
00:31:34,139 --> 00:31:34,840
the...

808
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:38,440
density of charge...

809
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:40,260
and the current of charge...

810
00:31:40,260 --> 00:31:41,600
are not invariants.

811
00:31:42,879 --> 00:31:43,680
For example...

812
00:31:45,219 --> 00:31:47,260
if I have a given charge...

813
00:31:47,260 --> 00:31:48,960
and I look at it in a...

814
00:31:48,960 --> 00:31:50,440
different frame of reference...

815
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:51,540
here's my charge...

816
00:31:51,540 --> 00:31:52,660
but I walk by it...

817
00:31:52,660 --> 00:31:53,440
I have trouble doing it...

818
00:31:53,440 --> 00:31:56,420
I walk by it with a certain velocity...

819
00:31:56,420 --> 00:31:57,320
I think I did that pretty well,

820
00:31:57,320 --> 00:31:57,700
didn't I?

821
00:31:59,059 --> 00:31:59,459
Yeah...

822
00:31:59,459 --> 00:31:59,860
okay...

823
00:31:59,860 --> 00:32:01,360
I'll try it again...

824
00:32:03,319 --> 00:32:03,719
Yeah...

825
00:32:03,719 --> 00:32:04,120
good...

826
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:07,980
And because of...

827
00:32:09,280 --> 00:32:10,440
Lorentz contraction...

828
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:13,160
I say that the volume of that...

829
00:32:13,160 --> 00:32:14,320
charge is one thing...

830
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:16,820
You sitting still assign a different...

831
00:32:16,820 --> 00:32:18,120
volume to it...

832
00:32:18,120 --> 00:32:21,360
One of us assigns a smaller volume...

833
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:22,840
Let's say you assign a bigger volume...

834
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:25,000
I assign a smaller volume because I see it...

835
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:26,500
Lorentz contracted...

836
00:32:27,030 --> 00:32:29,080
If we take the charge and we divide it by...

837
00:32:29,080 --> 00:32:29,480
the volume,

838
00:32:29,480 --> 00:32:31,160
we will not agree...

839
00:32:31,160 --> 00:32:33,160
about the value of the...

840
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:35,300
of the charge density...

841
00:32:35,300 --> 00:32:36,680
But that's okay...

842
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:38,800
Charge density is the component...

843
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:40,020
of a four vector...

844
00:32:40,020 --> 00:32:41,640
It's not an invariant...

845
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:45,060
Charge density is a component...

846
00:32:45,060 --> 00:32:46,120
of a four vector...

847
00:32:47,040 --> 00:32:47,640
Similarly...

848
00:32:47,640 --> 00:32:49,760
You see charges...

849
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:49,920
Well,

850
00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:50,380
let's say...

851
00:32:50,380 --> 00:32:53,300
You see charges standing still...

852
00:32:53,300 --> 00:32:55,560
And you say there is no current...

853
00:32:55,560 --> 00:32:56,340
Why?

854
00:32:56,340 --> 00:32:57,880
The charges are at rest...

855
00:32:57,880 --> 00:32:58,740
All of them...

856
00:32:58,740 --> 00:33:00,790
I'm moving and I see

857
00:33:00,790 --> 00:33:02,840
a wind of charges passing me...

858
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:04,480
I say there's current...

859
00:33:04,980 --> 00:33:05,280
Right?

860
00:33:07,120 --> 00:33:07,120
So,

861
00:33:07,120 --> 00:33:07,260
yes...

862
00:33:07,260 --> 00:33:10,240
Charge density and charge current...

863
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:11,480
are not invariants...

864
00:33:11,480 --> 00:33:13,700
They form together a four vector...

865
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:16,080
Now...

866
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:18,700
Energy and momentum are more complicated...

867
00:33:18,700 --> 00:33:21,000
The total energy and momentum...

868
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:23,100
Not the density of them...

869
00:33:23,100 --> 00:33:25,360
But the total energy and momentum...

870
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:27,240
are not invariant...

871
00:33:28,900 --> 00:33:31,580
